article.headline: Cleveland St. 85, CS Northridge 76
article.story: LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Joe Davis scored 17 points in 24 minutes to snap Cleveland State out of a five-game losing streak with an 85-76 victory over Cal State Northridge on Saturday night. Raheem Moss and J'Nathan Bullock added 16 points each for Cleveland State. Thomas Shewmake had 16 points and 11 rebounds to lead Northridge and Calvin Chitwood added 15 points. The Vikings outscored the Matadors 17-8 in the final 2:39 of the Bracket Buster game. The key difference in the game was free throws. Cleveland State was 30-40 from the line while the Matadors were only 15-18. It was the first-ever matchup between the two teams. Cleveland State (9-19) is ninth and last in the Horizon League while Northridge (12-14) is seventh in the Big West Conference.
